SOLAR and SPACE WEATHER (January 7, 2003)

3-Day Solar Forecast
Solar activity is expected to be low.

3-Day Aurora Forecast
Earth's geomagnetic field is expected to be at quiet to unsettled levels.

Solar Data
The current sunspot number is 128, and the solar wind speed recently clocked in at 399 kilometers per second.

The solar wind density was 1.7 protons per cubic centimeter.

(Speed and density values are snapshots in time and change during the day.)

